10:03 AM Defendant CODY M DENTER in court, in custody.  Attorney William Scott Nelson appeared by video for CODY M DENTER.  Attorney Matt McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls 22CF181, 22CF113 and 22CF114. Atty Nelson represents the defendant in 22CF113 and 22CF114. Court questions Atty Nelson on the motion filed to modify bond. Statement by Atty Nelson regarding bond modification. Court denies motion to modify bond. Court informs defendant to contact the public defender's office for 22CF181. 

22CF181 Preliminary Hearing. Court goes over right to Preliminary hearing or defendant can waive the time limits. Defendant requests to proceed with the prelim. State has two witnesses.

Amy Thoma, sworn, direct by ADA, is employed as the Clerk of Court for Green Lake County. Testimony given. ADA offers exhibit 1 and exhibit 2. No objection by defendant. Court accepts exhibits 1 and 2into evidence. Court takes judicial notice for 22CF114. No cross examination.

Samantha Koscher sworn, direct by ADA, is employed as a Corrections Sergeant for Green Lake County Correctional Facility. Testimony given. Identified the defendant - present in court. No cross examination. 

Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony has been committed and that the felony probably was committed by the defendant and binds the defendant over for trial. 

Court will set for Arraignment on December 5, 2022 at 10:30 AM with the other cases.

Court adjourned at 10:14 AM.
Preliminary hearing on November 1, 2022 at 10:00 am.
